The paper discusses the application of a general tension-reduction (GTR) model to explain the success of quantum probabilities in describing experimental situations in quantum models of cognition and decision. This suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as well as cryptography (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses psychological measurements, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
